│   ├── reviews.txt
│   └── bestsellers.txt
│
├── templates/
│   ├── dashboard.html
│   ├── catalog.html
│   ├── book_details.html
│   ├── cart.html
│   ├── checkout.html
│   ├── order_history.html
│   ├── reviews.html
│   ├── write_review.html
│   └── bestsellers.html
│
└── static/
    ├── css/
    │   └── styles.css
    ├── js/
    │   └── scripts.js
    └── images/
        └── (book cover images, icons, etc.)
```

### File Descriptions
- **app.py**  
  The main backend Python application file. It handles all routing, data processing, reading/writing to local text files, and rendering templates. Since the application is not very complex, consolidating backend logic into this single file simplifies maintenance and deployment.

- **data/**  
  Directory containing all local text files used for data storage as specified in the requirements. Each file corresponds to a specific data entity (books, categories, cart, orders, order items, reviews, bestsellers).

- **templates/**  
  Contains all HTML template files for the nine pages of the web application. Each file corresponds to one page as per the design document:
  - `dashboard.html` — Dashboard Page
  - `catalog.html` — Book Catalog Page
  - `book_details.html` — Book Details Page
  - `cart.html` — Shopping Cart Page
  - `checkout.html` — Checkout Page
  - `order_history.html` — Order History Page
  - `reviews.html` — Customer Reviews Page
  - `write_review.html` — Write Review Page
  - `bestsellers.html` — Bestsellers Page

- **static/**  
  Contains static assets such as CSS stylesheets, JavaScript files, and images:
  - `css/styles.css` — Stylesheet for consistent styling across pages.
  - `js/scripts.js` — JavaScript for client-side interactivity (e.g., button actions, form validations).
  - `images/` — Folder for book cover images and other graphical assets.

This structure cleanly separates backend logic, data storage, presentation templates, and static resources, facilitating straightforward development, testing, and future enhancements."

